THE WINES OF LUXEMBOURG

The vineyards of Germany border one side of the Moselle—the vineyards of Luxembourg the other. The wines are similar although Luxembourg does not produce the equivalent of a Berncasteler Doktor or Wehlener Sonnenuhr. These wines offer the advantage of low price, freshness, dry delicacy, and in- terest.

THE WINES OF JAPAN
